%F A071943 G.f.=(1-q)/[z(2t+2t^2z-1+q)], where q=sqrt(1-4tz-4t^2z^2).
%F A071943 Define T(0,0)=1 and T(n,k)=0 for k<0 and k >n. Then the array is generated by the recurrence T(n,k) = T(n,k-1) + T(n-1,k) + T(n-1,k-2). For example, T(5,3) = 46 = T(5,2) + T(4,3) + T(4,1) = 18 + 24 + 4. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Mar 28 2013
%e A071943 T(3,2)=7 because we have RRRVV, RRVRV, RRVVR, RVRRV, RVRVR, RRD and RDR.
